The cuckoo's voice signals departure in the **breast-hoard** (the heart/chest). In paragraph [p-f52e2e] of chapter 5, the speaker describes the cuckoo — "summer's warden" — calling with a mournful cry that sows "sorrow bitter in the breast-hoard," stirring within the speaker an irresistible longing to set out across the flood-ways.
